attributes.magic: PE32 executable (GUI) Intel 80386, for MS Windows

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Identifies metasploit wininet reverse shellcode. Also used by other tools (like beacon).
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Elastic Security

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a malicious loader or downloader that exhibits several high-confidence indicators of malware. It utilizes a custom RWX section (.rnny) for its entry point, which is typical for shellcode or packed payloads. The code performs manual API resolution by walking the Process Environment Block (PEB) LDR structures and using an ROR13 hashing algorithm to identify exports, a common technique to evade static import analysis. It attempts to modify its own memory permissions using VirtualProtect (PAGE_EXECUTE_READWRITE) and contains hardcoded artifacts for network communication, including a specific Mozilla Firefox User-Agent string and a suspicious URI path (/mm13/-gXdviw...) likely used for C2 interaction via the WinInet library.
